  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nPierogi\nNormal\nPig Fiesta\nFood Info\n37.5\n40\n5\nMeat\nObject Info\n20 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 >0.25 >0.25 x1\n20 sec\n5\nMiscellaneous\n\"perogies\"\n“These turned out pretty good.”\n–Wilson\n“Tasty things, sealed with fire.”\n–Willow\n“Wolfgang love pierogi!”\n–Wolfgang\n“A lovely little pouch of nutrients.”\n–Wendy\n“LIKE MEATY BATTERY PACKS”\n–WX-78\n“A wonderfully bland dumpling.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I call them \"Yum pockets\".”\n–Woodie\n“I made it, so you know it's good.”\n–Maxwell\n“Pockets of victuals.”\n–Wagstaff\n“Pöckets öf meat.”\n–Wigfrid\n“It does not look like pie...”\n–Webber\n“Comfort food!”\n–Walani\n“Mmmmm, pockets of palate punching pleasure!”\n–Warly\n“Woodlegs could eat a chest full o'these!”\n–Woodlegs\n“POCKET O' FOODS”\n–Wilba\n“Good belly stuff”\n–Wormwood\n“Food. For me or the Pew-matic.”\n–Wheeler\n“You work up a mighty appetite at the factory.”\n–Winona\n“Mortal food, this seems to be.”\n–Wortox\n“Glurgh, hid meat inside??”\n–Wurt\n“The perfect size to pop in your mouth!”\n–Walter\n“Little pockets of food.”\n–Wanda\nPierogi is a Meat Food Item cooked in the Crock Pot by adding 1 Egg, more than 0.25 Meat Units and more than 0.25 Vegetable Units. It takes 20 seconds to cook.\nAdding 2 Monster Foods will result in Monster Lasagna. Adding 1 Mandrake will result in Mandrake Soup. Adding 1 Twig will result in Kabobs.\nIn Don't Starve Together using Pepper as the vegetable or filler will instead result in Stuffed Pepper Poppers.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:\nRequires:\nRequires:\nExcludes:\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\nFiller cannot be Twigs.\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\nA recipe for Pierogi that extenuates a lot of useful hunger value.\n×2\nTips[edit | edit source]\nPierogi replenish as much hunger as Honey Nuggets, but heal for a substantial amount of health (40 health, 10 more than Honey Poultice). It requires Eggs from a Birdcage, which is relatively resource-intensive to craft (or a Tallbird Egg, although there are better uses for it), which means it can take a while before one is able to reliably make this recipe, but it can easily become a source of healing for a well-prepared survivor.\nPierogi have an exceptional spoilage time of 20 days, which makes them a good alternative for Honey Poultice while making long expeditions, or if one needs to increase the longevity of their meat stock.\nBacon and Eggs have an identical spoilage time and can be made with almost the same recipe (substituting a Vegetable with an Egg), though it restores twice the hunger at the cost of half the health. As such, Bacon and Eggs are better for expeditions where one will expect to take some damage, but still require filling a half-empty belly.\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nDuring the Pig Fiesta event in the Hamlet DLC, Pierogi take on a more festive appearance, resembling steamed dumplings.\nIn Poland, \"Pierogi\" is a dish similar to the Asian dumplings. The Pierogi image in the Don't Starve game files is called \"perogies\" (another try on pierogi), but the in-game item is based on polish version of the dish.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nWebber and Wickerbottom cooking Pierogi in a Lunar New Year promo image.\nOriginal HD icon from Bonus Materials from CD Don't Starve.\nIcon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
