  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|canBeBurned=1\n|foodRecipe = {{Pic|32px|Eggs}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Meats}}>0.25 {{Pic|32px|Vegetables}}>0.25 {{Pic|32px|Filler}}x1\n|icon =<gallery>\nPierogi.png|Normal\nPierogi (Pig Fiesta).png|Pig Fiesta\n</gallery>\n|foodType = [[Food_Type#Meat|Meat]] [[File:Meats.png|32px|link=Food_Type#Meat]]\n|image = Pierogi Dropped.png\n|spoil          = 20 Days\n|stack          = 40\n|hpRestored     = 40\n|hungerRestored = 37.5\n|sanityRestored = 5\n|cooktime       = 20 sec\n|priority       = 5\n|spawnCode      = \"perogies\"}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = These turned out pretty good.\n|willow = Tasty things, sealed with fire.\n|wolfgang = Wolfgang love pierogi!\n|wendy = A lovely little pouch of nutrients.\n|wx78 = LIKE MEATY BATTERY PACKS\n|wickerbottom = A wonderfully bland dumpling.\n|woodie = I call them \"Yum pockets\".\n|maxwell = I made it, so you know it's good.\n|wagstaff = Pockets of victuals.\n|wigfrid = Pöckets öf meat.\n|webber = It does not look like pie...\n|walani = Comfort food!\n|warly = Mmmmm, pockets of palate punching pleasure!\n|woodlegs = Woodlegs could eat a chest full o'these!\n|wilba = POCKET O' FOODS\n|wormwood = Good belly stuff\n|wheeler = Food. For me or the Pew-matic.\n|winona = You work up a mighty appetite at the factory.\n|wortox = Mortal food, this seems to be.\n|wurt = Glurgh, hid meat inside??\n|walter = The perfect size to pop in your mouth!\n|wanda = Little pockets of food.\n|choose = wolfgang\n}}\n'''Pierogi''' is a [[Food Type#Meat|Meat]] [[Food|Food]] [[Items|Item]] cooked in the [[Crock Pot]] by adding 1 [[Food Value#Egg Value|Egg]], more than 0.25 [[food Value#Meat Value|Meat Units]] and more than 0.25 [[food Value#Vegetable Value|Vegetable Units]]. It takes 20 seconds to cook.\n\nAdding 2 [[Monster Food]]s will result in [[Monster Lasagna]]. Adding 1 [[Mandrake]] will result in [[Mandrake Soup]]. Adding 1 [[Twigs|Twig]] will result in [[Kabobs]].\n\nIn ''[[Don't Starve Together]]'' using [[Pepper]] as the vegetable or filler will instead result in [[Stuffed Pepper Poppers]].\n\n__NOTOC__\n== Prerequisites ==\n* Requires: [[File:Meats Crock Pot(NoMoleworm).png|link=Meats]]\n* Requires: [[File:Eggs Crock Pot.png|link=Eggs]]\n* Requires: [[File:Crock Pot Vegetables (no Mandrake).png|link=Vegetables]]\n* Excludes: [[File:Twigs.png|link=Twigs]][[File:Mandrake.png|link=Mandrake]]\n\n== {{pic|32|Cookbook}} Recipe ==\n{{Recipe\n|item2 = Eggs\n|item1 = Meats\n|item3 = Vegetables\n|item4 = Filler\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Pierogi\n|note = Filler cannot be [[Twigs]].\n}}\n\n== Examples ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Monster Meat\n|item2 = Egg\n|item3 = Red Cap\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Pierogi\n|note={{Pic24|Prototype}} A recipe for Pierogi that extenuates a lot of useful hunger value.}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Morsel\n|item2 = Egg\n|item3 = Carrot\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Pierogi\n|item4=Ice}}{{Recipe\n|item1 = Monster Meat\n|item2 = Egg\n|item3 = Kelp Fronds\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Pierogi\n}}{{Recipe\n|item1 = Monster Meat\n|item2 = Egg\n|item3 = Ripe Stone Fruit\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Pierogi\n|item4=Ripe Stone Fruit}}{{Recipe\n|item1 = Monster Meat\n|item2 = Egg\n|item3 = Cactus Flesh\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Pierogi\n|item4=Cactus Flower}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Monster Meats\n|item2 = Small Eggs\n|item3 = Seaweed\n|item4 = Ice\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Pierogi\n|dlc = Shipwrecked\n}}{{Recipe|item1=Monster Meats|item2=Small Eggs|item3=Seaweed|item4=Seaweed|note=|pot=yes|result=Pierogi|dlc=Shipwrecked}}\n=={{pic|32|Prototype}} Tips ==\n*Pierogi replenish as much hunger as [[Honey Nuggets]], but heal for a substantial amount of health (40 health, 10 more than [[Honey Poultice]]). It requires Eggs from a [[Birdcage]], which is relatively resource-intensive to craft (or a [[Tallbird Egg]], although there are better uses for it), which means it can take a while before one is able to reliably make this recipe, but it can easily become a source of healing for a well-prepared survivor.\n*Pierogi have an exceptional spoilage time of 20 days, which makes them a good alternative for Honey Poultice while making long expeditions, or if one needs to increase the longevity of their meat stock.\n**[[Bacon and Eggs]] have an identical spoilage time and can be made with almost the same recipe (substituting a Vegetable with an Egg), though it restores twice the hunger at the cost of half the health. As such, Bacon and Eggs are better for expeditions where one will expect to take some damage, but still require filling a half-empty belly.\n== {{pic|32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n* During the [[Pig Fiesta]] event in the ''[[Don't Starve: Hamlet|Hamlet]]'' DLC, Pierogi take on a more festive appearance, resembling [[wikipedia:Dumpling#East_Asian|steamed dumplings]].\n* In Poland, \"Pierogi\" is a dish similar to the Asian dumplings. The Pierogi image in the ''Don't Starve'' game files is called \"perogies\" (another try on pierogi), but the in-game item is based on polish version of the dish.\n\n== {{Pic|32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nLunarpromo.png|[[Webber]] and [[Wickerbottom]] cooking Pierogi in a Lunar New Year promo image.\nCD perogies.png|Original HD icon from Bonus Materials from [[CD Don't Starve]].\nPierogi 128x128.png|Icon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord.\n</gallery>\n\n{{Crock Pot Food}}\n[[pl:Pierogi]]\n[[ru:Вареники]]\n[[fr:Pierogi]]\n[[vi:Sủi Cảo]]\n[[Category:Flammable Objects]]\n[[Category:Healing]]\n[[Category:Perishables]]\n[[Category:Sanity Boost]]\n[[Category:Crock Pot Recipes]]"
